## Ray Tracing Simulation with Gradient Effects
A real-time 2D ray tracing simulation built with C and SDL2, featuring dynamic lighting, shadow casting, and beautiful gradient effects.
Features

- Interactive Light Source: Drag the yellow circle to move the light source around the screen
- Dynamic Shadows: A blocking object (grey circle) casts realistic shadows as light rays are obstructed
- Gradient Rays: Rays transition from bright orange to dark purple, creating a stunning sunset effect
- Real-time Rendering: Smooth 60 FPS interactive visualization
- Draggable Objects: Both the light source and shadow-casting object can be moved with your mouse

### Prerequisites
To compile and run this program, you need:

- GCC or another C compiler
- SDL2 development libraries